author: Gillian Wong
title: Alibaba Lobbies U.S. Government to Be Kept Off Piracy Blacklist
text:
BEIJING—Faced with increasing complaints about the sale of counterfeits on its websites, Alibaba Group Holding Ltd. is lobbying the U.S. government to keep its popular online bazaar and other trading platforms off its list of markets for pirated goods.
Alibaba has written to the U.S. Trade Representative’s office to highlight recent efforts to protect intellectual property, including a new mechanism the company introduced in April that is aimed at expediting requests from brands for fake merchandise to be taken off...
